The paper focuses on the scalability and performance reproducibility of parallel machine learning training algorithms, which is a core topic in the field of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the dataset characters that affect the scalability of the algorithms, which falls under the scope of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of AI techniques, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the convergence proof and design experiments, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning algorithms in computer vision, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
